`crates/ctx-brief/src` is the whole `ctx-brief` binary crate: turning a `docs/STATUS.md` backlog item or free-text ask into an executor brief via a two-stage `claude` CLI pipeline (gather, then plan). Depending on this crate means running the `ctx-brief` binary or, for tests, calling `cli::dispatch`/`runner::run` against the `Fs`/`Claude` trait seams.

Everything funnels through `main.rs` → `cli.rs` → `runner.rs`. `main.rs` wires real `StdFs`/`ClaudeCli`, resolves `--target` to an absolute, existing path, and handles `--contract` as a pre-clap bypass. `cli.rs` parses argv, derives the output path (`slug()` logic — the only place filenames are derived), and builds `runner::Config` with cwd-relative paths under `--target`. `runner.rs` is the actual orchestration: reads `status_item`-resolved backlog text, runs a restricted-tool `claude -p` gather pass, then either `headless_plan` (captures stdout, writes via `Fs`) or `interactive_plan` (human session writes the file itself, runner only verifies existence). Both Claude stages run with `cwd` set to the *target* repo so its own context hooks fire — this convention is asserted independently in `claude.rs` and relied on in `runner.rs`.

Shared invariants across children: all filesystem access goes through `fs::Fs` (never raw `std::fs` in runner/cli logic), all failures funnel into the single `BriefError` enum in `error.rs` (no `From` conversions — variants constructed explicitly), and no prompt text is ever inlined in Rust source (prompts load from `cfg.prompts_dir` by fixed filename, or are passed to Claude via `--append-system-prompt`/stdin/positional arg). `Config` carries two output-path variants (`out_rel` vs `out_fs`) that must not be conflated. `contract.rs`'s `CONTRACT` string must stay in sync with actual CLI behavior (flags, defaults, output convention) or the `contracts` battery check fails the build — any change to flags in `cli.rs`, output-path derivation, or the two-stage flow in `runner.rs` requires a matching edit there.

`status_item.rs` is self-contained parsing logic (STATUS.md table format, escaped-pipe cells) consumed only by `runner.rs`.